Now I try not to be a hard critique when patronizing these take out restaurants, especially if it is a place that I like and have frequented quite often. I usually go to this teriyaki spot on my lunch break ,and I have become very acquainted with the poke bowl since it it mostly seafood (shrimp, crabmeat) and salad, I have read the menu several times when ordering to make sure I am not getting an unwanted food item,(I don‚Äôt eat meat, to include chicken/lamb/beef, of any kind), I also have food allergies, mainly ( and I don‚Äôt know how, or why) zucchini. This food item is not listed as an item in the poke bowl, and I have ordered this many times, never has it ever had zucchini or cucumbers. I go in today for my usual order, as I am sitting in my car to have my lunch, I get past the top layer, and just under the second layer‚Ä¶WHAT DO I SEE? I almost had a heart attack, the food item that will have my throat closing in 2.2 seconds. I jump out of my car and run back across the street to have this order corrected, they tried to tell me nooo,it‚Äôs cucumber, very unconcerned, I said absolutely not,‚Ä¶ MY THROAT WILL CLOSE!, they offered to make the order over, my issue is, there was no apology or anything remotely close, I said all of that to say, to this establishment you need to be much more careful, if you do not have an item listed, DO NOT, I REPEAT, DO NOT put it in the food order, you don‚Äôt know what a person could be allergic to. This could have gone terribly wrong

If you fail at  making poke bowl you fail at doing everything.
